01:33:12,920 --> 01:33:14,717
First Platoon present and accounted for!

1227
01:33:14,800 --> 01:33:16,279
Second Platoon all accounted for!

1228
01:33:16,360 --> 01:33:18,396
Third Platoon all present
and accounted for!

1229
01:33:18,680 --> 01:33:20,796
Fourth Platoon all present
and accounted for!

1230
01:33:20,880 --> 01:33:22,393
Fifth Platoon all accounted for!

1231
01:33:22,880 --> 01:33:24,472
Sixth Platoon all accounted for!

1232
01:33:25,160 --> 01:33:27,594
Company, dismissed!

1233
01:33:32,400 --> 01:33:34,118
Prewis still absent.

1234
01:33:35,360 --> 01:33:36,998
Makes three days now.

1235
01:33:39,640 --> 01:33:42,632
How long are you gonna carry him present,
Top?

1236
01:33:43,040 --> 01:33:44,359
I just mention it.

1237
01:33:44,440 --> 01:33:46,351
Well, don't mention it.

1238
01:33:52,640 --> 01:33:55,473
"Upon observing these incidents,
an investigation was made...

1239
01:33:55,560 --> 01:33:59,348
"...by the Inspector General's Department
over a period of several months.

1240
01:33:59,480 --> 01:34:01,232
"It was found that Captain Holmes...

1241
01:34:01,320 --> 01:34:05,029
"...has been guilty of indefensible cruelty
to the aforesaid Private Prewitt.

1242
01:34:05,120 --> 01:34:08,874
"As mentioned, this included instigation
of wholly unauthorised tactics...

1243
01:34:09,040 --> 01:34:13,033
"...to force the soldier
to join the interregiment boxing team."

1244
01:34:17,920 --> 01:34:19,717
I'm waiting for your reply.

1245
01:34:20,280 --> 01:34:21,554
I haven't any, sir.

1246
01:34:23,720 --> 01:34:27,872
First thing I learned in the Army
was that an officer takes care of his men.

1247
01:34:27,960 --> 01:34:30,520
It seems to be the first thing you forgot.

1248
01:34:30,680 --> 01:34:31,874
My only regret is...

1249
01:34:31,960 --> 01:34:35,236
...we have to keep you in uniform
till a court-martial is concluded.

1250
01:34:35,960 --> 01:34:38,633
If there were any way
to avoid a court-martial, sir.

1251
01:34:39,840 --> 01:34:43,355
There is one alternative, General,
if you are so disposed:

1252
01:34:43,600 --> 01:34:47,513
A resignation for the good of the service
under Army regulations.

1253
01:34:48,680 --> 01:34:50,318
Write a letter of resignation.

1254
01:34:50,440 --> 01:34:52,476
Have it on my desk this afternoon.

1255
01:34:52,600 --> 01:34:54,192
As far as I'm concerned...

1256
01:34:54,440 --> 01:34:57,159
...the quicker you're out,
the better for everybody...

1257
01:34:57,280 --> 01:34:59,350
...especially the Army.

1258
01:35:00,640 --> 01:35:02,358
Thas all, Holmes.

1259
01:35:09,560 --> 01:35:11,835
I know whas been going on in this outfit.

1260
01:35:11,920 --> 01:35:14,229
I know how far some of you
have been out of line.

1261
01:35:14,560 --> 01:35:17,393
If you want to remain non-coms,
you'd better snap into it.

1262
01:35:17,560 --> 01:35:18,754
And another thing:

1263
01:35:19,120 --> 01:35:22,430
From now on,
no man will earn his stripes by boxing.

1264
01:35:24,720 --> 01:35:26,790
- Get rid of those.
- Yes, sir.

1265
01:35:27,400 --> 01:35:28,753
Dismissed.

1266
01:35:34,520 --> 01:35:36,715
- About Sergeant Galovitch.
- Yes, sir.

1267
01:35:36,800 --> 01:35:39,519
Bust him. Sergeant Galovitch
is now Private Galovitch.

1268
01:35:39,600 --> 01:35:41,989
Put him in charge of the latrine.

1269
01:35:42,160 --> 01:35:43,388
What are you grinning at?

1270
01:35:43,480 --> 01:35:46,995
I think the Company Commander
made a wise decision, sir.

1271
01:35:48,880 --> 01:35:50,836
Company G, Captain Ross.

1272
01:35:52,560 --> 01:35:53,834
Just a minute.

1273
01:35:53,920 --> 01:35:56,753
- Is for you, Sergeant.
- Thank you, sir.

1274
01:35:59,160 --> 01:36:00,434
Yes, sir.

1275
01:36:03,360 --> 01:36:05,999
Yes, the parcel has already arrived.

1276
01:36:07,440 --> 01:36:08,429
What?

1277
01:36:08,600 --> 01:36:10,875
I've got to see you, Milt. Is important.

1278
01:36:14,120 --> 01:36:15,792
Okay, I'll get away somehow.

1279
01:36:15,920 --> 01:36:18,878
Sure, thad be fine, yeah.

1280
01:36:19,240 --> 01:36:21,913
I'll be there in about an hour. Right.

1281
01:36:25,600 --> 01:36:29,639
He's being sent back to the States,
sailing next week, and wants me to go.

1282
01:36:29,720 --> 01:36:30,755
What will we do?

1283
01:36:32,800 --> 01:36:35,758
When do you think
you'll get your commission?

1284
01:36:38,480 --> 01:36:42,314
I didn't put it in.
I filled it out, but I didn't sign it.

1285
01:36:42,720 --> 01:36:46,633
I took it out of my desk a dozen times,
but I couldn't sign it.

1286
01:36:47,040 --> 01:36:48,029
Why?

1287
01:36:49,560 --> 01:36:51,994
- But it was the plan...
- I know.

1288
01:36:52,160 --> 01:36:53,559
Is been weeks.

1289
01:36:53,640 --> 01:36:55,835
You can't say you'll do a thing
and not do it.

1290
01:36:55,920 --> 01:36:57,148
Karen, listen to me.

1291
01:36:57,240 --> 01:37:00,516
Why didn't you do it?
Why didn't you tell me?

1292
01:37:01,600 --> 01:37:03,352
Be back in a minute.

1293
01:37:05,880 --> 01:37:08,633
Sorry, I thought you were somebody else.

1294
01:37:14,240 --> 01:37:17,835
I thought it was a guy from our company,
Prewitt, the kid I told you about.

1295
01:37:17,920 --> 01:37:20,639
He got mixed up with a girl
at the New Congress Club.

1296
01:37:20,720 --> 01:37:23,553
He's AWOL, probably in lots of trouble.

1297
01:37:23,880 --> 01:37:26,713
Robert E. Lee Prewitt, a crazy, no-good...

1298
01:37:29,720 --> 01:37:32,792
Karen, I'm no officer. I'm an enlisted man.

1299
01:37:33,200 --> 01:37:34,269
I can't be anything else.

1300
01:37:34,360 --> 01:37:36,749
If I try to be an officer,
I'll be putting on an act.

1301
01:37:36,840 --> 01:37:40,310
I just can't do it. Please don't ask me why.

1302
01:37:41,960 --> 01:37:43,313
I know why.

1303
01:37:44,280 --> 01:37:46,430
You don't have to become an officer now...

1304
01:37:46,520 --> 01:37:48,954
...now that Dana's out of the Army.

1305
01:37:49,160 --> 01:37:51,435
You just don't want to marry me.

1306
01:37:51,520 --> 01:37:53,988
You're already married to the Army.

1307
01:37:54,160 --> 01:37:55,832
I love you, Karen.

1308
01:38:01,080 --> 01:38:02,672
I know.

1309
01:38:05,320 --> 01:38:06,799
I don't want you to go back to Holmes.

1310
01:38:06,960 --> 01:38:09,428
I don't want to, either. But I am.

1311
01:38:09,640 --> 01:38:11,949
There's nothing else for me to do.

1312
01:38:12,240 --> 01:38:15,118
Is no good with us, Milt.
It could never have been any good.

1313
01:38:15,200 --> 01:38:16,838
Hiding, sneaking.

1314
01:38:17,240 --> 01:38:18,958
It had to wear out.

1315
01:38:22,320 --> 01:38:24,038
Good-bye, Sergeant.

1316
01:38:24,760 --> 01:38:27,194
- Thanks.
- It ain't good-bye, is...

1317
01:38:28,200 --> 01:38:30,839
We'll see each other again, somewhere.

1318
01:38:31,880 --> 01:38:34,758
Of course we will. Somewhere.

1319
01:38:48,840 --> 01:38:49,989
Here it is.

1320
01:38:50,080 --> 01:38:52,469
Got it on the inside page already.

1321
01:38:53,320 --> 01:38:54,435
"Still no clue...

1322
01:38:54,640 --> 01:38:57,791
"...in the fatal stabbing
of Staff Sergeant James R. Judson."

1323
01:38:58,800 --> 01:39:00,392
Did you hear me?

1324
01:39:03,520 --> 01:39:05,795
Are you trying to set a new worlïs record?

1325
01:39:07,760 --> 01:39:09,955
Yeah, as a matter of fact, I am.

1326
01:39:11,200 --> 01:39:13,509
To the memory of Robert E. Lee Prewitt...

1327
01:39:13,960 --> 01:39:16,952
...holder of the new worlïs record.

1328
01:39:34,200 --> 01:39:36,668
- Everything all right, Top?
- Great.

1329
01:39:36,840 --> 01:39:40,230
This is a beautiful meal to put in front
of a guy on a Sunday morning.

1330
01:39:40,320 --> 01:39:41,912
Congratulations.

1331
01:39:55,640 --> 01:39:57,676
They sure look pretty
over them mountains.

1332
01:39:57,760 --> 01:39:59,079
Don't they, though?

1333
01:40:07,880 --> 01:40:10,348
Sounds like they're dynamiting
down at Wheeler Field.

1334
01:40:10,440 --> 01:40:14,228
Mighty ambitious.
Sunday morning before 8:00?

1335
01:40:26,080 --> 01:40:29,516
The Japs are bombing Wheeler Field!

1336
01:40:29,600 --> 01:40:31,875
I've seen the red circles on the...

1337
01:41:01,800 --> 01:41:03,870
Get out of here. Hurry up! Go!

1338
01:41:07,920 --> 01:41:09,990
This is a real attack, not a manoeuvre.

1339
01:41:10,080 --> 01:41:12,310
The Japanese are bombing Pearl Harbor.

1340
01:41:12,400 --> 01:41:14,755
Please keep in your homes.
Do not go on the streets.

1341
01:41:14,840 --> 01:41:16,114
This is a real attack.

1342
01:41:16,200 --> 01:41:19,590
Japanese planes are bombing
our Naval and Army installations.

1343
01:41:23,520 --> 01:41:24,873
- Quiet down!
- At ease!

1344
01:41:25,160 --> 01:41:28,948
Non-coms, get BARs and ammunition
from the supply room. Get up on the roof.

1345
01:41:29,040 --> 01:41:30,029
Anderson!

1346
01:41:30,520 --> 01:41:33,239
You're in charge of the loading detail.
Get moving.

1347
01:41:33,720 --> 01:41:35,199
Rest of you men, listen to me.

1348
01:41:35,320 --> 01:41:38,790
Every man get his rifle, go to his bunk
and stay there. And I mean...

1349
01:41:38,880 --> 01:41:40,711
...stay there!

1350
01:41:41,480 --> 01:41:45,359
Shut up! You'll get your ears shot off
if you go outside.

1351
01:41:45,440 --> 01:41:49,194
You'll get plenty of chances to be heroes
with Japs in your lap before night.

1352
01:41:49,360 --> 01:41:51,828
Now get moving, we're wasting time!

1353
01:41:55,640 --> 01:41:59,519
Into the kitchen and make a pot of coffee.
Wait a minute, a barrel of coffee!

1354
01:42:19,160 --> 01:42:21,754
I can't issue live ammunition
without a signed order.

1355
01:42:21,840 --> 01:42:24,593
- The Captain ain't here, jerk!
- Sorry. No order, no ammo.

1356
01:42:24,680 --> 01:42:26,477
- Whas the matter?
- I got my orders!

1357
01:42:26,560 --> 01:42:29,028
Army regulations state that I can't...

1358
01:42:33,480 --> 01:42:34,959
you blind? Give me the key!

1359
01:42:35,040 --> 01:42:37,554
- I got to obey orders, Top.
- I'll see you get a medal!

1360
01:42:37,640 --> 01:42:40,074
- Bust it down, boys!
- I warned you!

1361
01:43:02,480 --> 01:43:04,311
Don't go out, Warden, you'll get killed!

1362
01:43:04,400 --> 01:43:06,914
Put your pants on. You'll catch cold!

1363
01:43:32,760 --> 01:43:34,432
Give them a hand with this ammo!

1364
01:43:34,640 --> 01:43:35,834
Put that stuff over there.

1365
01:43:41,760 --> 01:43:44,194
Watch your fire, boys,
and lead those planes!

1366
01:44:04,000 --> 01:44:06,389
Friday's gone crazy!
He's blowing the Cavalry Charge!

1367
01:44:09,920 --> 01:44:11,114
Here they come, boys!

1368
01:44:41,720 --> 01:44:43,472
I got him, Pete! I got him!

1369
01:44:43,920 --> 01:44:45,512
I got him!

1370
01:44:53,400 --> 01:44:55,789
The danger of an invasion
continues to exist.

1371
01:44:55,880 --> 01:44:58,952
Infantry from Schofield Barracks
moved out within a few hours...

1372
01:44:59,040 --> 01:45:00,837
...and have manned beach positions.

1373
01:45:00,920 --> 01:45:02,353
This is no manoeuvre.

1374
01:45:02,480 --> 01:45:04,391
This is the real McCoy.

1375
01:45:04,680 --> 01:45:06,272
Look out for falling shrapnel.

1376
01:45:06,560 --> 01:45:07,913
Keep under cover.

1377
01:45:08,000 --> 01:45:11,595
Blackout and curfew restrictions
will be rigidly enforced.

1378
01:45:11,800 --> 01:45:14,678
Stay in your homes.
Don't use the telephone.

1379
01:45:15,720 --> 01:45:19,269
Rest assured that immediate relay
to you of any and all information...

1380
01:45:19,400 --> 01:45:21,391
We've been to Queen's Hospital
giving blood.

1381
01:45:21,480 --> 01:45:22,515
The town's a madhouse!

1382
01:45:22,600 --> 01:45:24,352
A big house was bombed on Kuhio Street.

1383
01:45:24,440 --> 01:45:27,159
The drugstore down on McNully
and King is smashed flat!

1384
01:45:27,360 --> 01:45:28,759
A man and his wife were killed.

1385
01:45:28,960 --> 01:45:32,953
Your attention, please.
Listen to this carefully and keep calm.

1386
01:45:33,160 --> 01:45:36,118
The danger of an invasion
continues to exist.

1387
01:45:36,200 --> 01:45:39,795
And the planes have been identified
as Japanese planes.

1388
01:45:40,760 --> 01:45:42,796
Who do they think they're fighting?

1389
01:45:42,960 --> 01:45:46,475
They're picking trouble
with the best Army in the world.

1390
01:45:47,880 --> 01:45:48,995
Where you going?

1391
01:45:50,240 --> 01:45:52,834
I gotta get back to the company.

1392
01:45:53,040 --> 01:45:55,554
The company? But why?

1393
01:45:56,040 --> 01:45:57,109
Why?

1394
01:45:57,520 --> 01:45:59,988
But you can't. You're not well yet.

1395
01:46:00,440 --> 01:46:02,874
You're AWOL.
They'll throw you in the stockade.

1396
01:46:03,360 --> 01:46:06,591
They'll be throwing them out
of the stockade. They need everyone.

1397
01:46:06,680 --> 01:46:08,238
But your side'll open up.

1398
01:46:08,840 --> 01:46:11,195
They'll find out you killed that soldier.

1399
01:46:11,480 --> 01:46:14,438
Once I report in to the company,
they'll take care of me.

1400
01:46:14,520 --> 01:46:16,078
I'll be all right once I get back.

1401
01:46:16,160 --> 01:46:19,436
But you'll never make it!
There's patrols all over!

1402
01:46:19,680 --> 01:46:22,114
I'll make it. I know a shortcut.

1403
01:46:24,920 --> 01:46:26,751
Prew, stay till morning.

1404
01:46:26,840 --> 01:46:29,434
Maybe if you stay till morning
you'll change your mind.

1405
01:46:36,720 --> 01:46:38,517
Prew, don't go!

1406
01:46:39,000 --> 01:46:40,558
I'll do anything you want.

1407
01:46:41,440 --> 01:46:45,149
We can go back to the States together,
we can even get married.

1408
01:46:48,480 --> 01:46:51,392
If you go now,
I'll never see you again, I know it.

1409
01:46:52,080 --> 01:46:53,195
I'm sorry.

1410
01:46:58,240 --> 01:47:00,595
What do you want to go back
to the Army for?

1411
01:47:00,680 --> 01:47:03,478
What did the Army do for you
besides treat you like dirt...

1412
01:47:03,560 --> 01:47:05,357
...and give you one awful going over?

1413
01:47:05,440 --> 01:47:09,433
Get your friend killed!
What do you want to go back for?

1414
01:47:09,560 --> 01:47:12,028
What do I want to go back for?
I'm a soldier.

1415
01:47:12,560 --> 01:47:16,030
A soldier! A regular.
From the regular Army!

1416
01:47:16,120 --> 01:47:17,678
A 30-year man!

1417
01:47:19,440 --> 01:47:23,228
I got to turn off the lights,
'cause of the blackout outside.

1418
01:47:36,560 --> 01:47:39,154
They say they've seen parachutists
land up in the hills.

1419
01:47:39,240 --> 01:47:40,514
I ain't worried about them.

1420
01:47:40,600 --> 01:47:42,431
Saboteurs is what worries me.

1421
01:47:42,520 --> 01:47:45,557
I bet they're operating
all over these islands.

1422
01:48:55,720 --> 01:48:56,709
Halt!

1423
01:48:59,480 --> 01:49:00,469
Halt!

1424
01:49:12,000 --> 01:49:12,989
Halt!

1425
01:49:48,120 --> 01:49:50,350
Do you know this man, Sergeant?

1426
01:49:50,520 --> 01:49:51,794
Yes, sir.

1427
01:49:52,240 --> 01:49:54,276
He didn't have any regular identification.

1428
01:49:54,360 --> 01:49:56,715
They found a card on him with his name.

1429
01:49:56,960 --> 01:49:58,791
Seems to be membership of a club:

1430
01:49:58,920 --> 01:50:00,751
The New Congress Club.

1431
01:50:01,120 --> 01:50:03,998
You'd better take care of these, Sergeant.

1432
01:50:07,000 --> 01:50:08,479
Was this man a friend of yours?

1433
01:50:08,600 --> 01:50:12,513
Yes, sir. He musve been trying to reach
our company position up the beach here.

1434
01:50:12,600 --> 01:50:14,238
Then why didn't he halt?

1435
01:50:14,320 --> 01:50:17,357
He was always a hardhead, sir,
but he was a good soldier.

1436
01:50:17,480 --> 01:50:19,869
He loved the Army
more than any soldier I ever knew.

1437
01:50:20,640 --> 01:50:23,234
I see. I'm sorry, Sergeant.

1438
01:50:38,440 --> 01:50:40,795
You just couldn't play it smart, could you?

1439
01:50:41,600 --> 01:50:45,115
All you had to do was box, but no,
not you, you hardhead.

1440
01:50:45,800 --> 01:50:50,112
Funny thing is, there ain't gonna be
any boxing championships this year.

1441
01:50:56,760 --> 01:50:59,069
Whas the matter?
Ain't you ever seen a dead man?

1442
01:50:59,160 --> 01:51:02,197
Les get this body out of here!
We ain't got all night!

1443
01:51:23,200 --> 01:51:25,191
Is very beautiful, isn't it?

1444
01:51:29,600 --> 01:51:33,149
I think is the most beautiful place
I ever saw in my life.

1445
01:51:34,640 --> 01:51:37,438
I can almost see where I worked from here.

1446
01:51:41,160 --> 01:51:42,798
There's a legend:

1447
01:51:44,000 --> 01:51:47,515
If they float in toward shore,
you'll come back some day.

1448
01:51:48,440 --> 01:51:49,998
If they float out to sea, you won't.

1449
01:51:55,640 --> 01:51:57,631
I won't come back.

1450
01:51:59,040 --> 01:52:01,759
My fiancé was killed on December 7.

1451
01:52:03,200 --> 01:52:04,553
I'm sorry.

1452
01:52:05,400 --> 01:52:07,231
He was a bomber pilot.

1453
01:52:07,440 --> 01:52:10,273
He tried to taxi his plane
to the edge of the apron.

1454
01:52:10,400 --> 01:52:12,709
The Japs made a direct hit on it.

1455
01:52:13,520 --> 01:52:16,159
Maybe you read about it in the papers.

1456
01:52:16,600 --> 01:52:18,750
He was awarded the Silver Star.

1457
01:52:19,800 --> 01:52:21,995
They sent it to his mother.

1458
01:52:22,200 --> 01:52:24,156
She wrote me she wanted me to have it.

1459
01:52:24,800 --> 01:52:26,756
Thas very fine of her.

1460
01:52:27,600 --> 01:52:30,478
They're very fine people. Southern people.

1461
01:52:31,360 --> 01:52:33,555
He was named after a general.

1462
01:52:34,360 --> 01:52:35,918
Robert E. Lee...

1463
01:52:36,760 --> 01:52:37,749
...Prewitt.

1464
01:52:39,840 --> 01:52:40,829
Who?

1465
01:52:42,480 --> 01:52:45,756
Robert E. Lee Prewitt.

1466
01:52:48,440 --> 01:52:50,032
Isn't that a silly old name?
